title: How to write your own programming language
text: Have you ever tried to program in Brainfuck? What about Chicken? If you're a fan of esoteric programming languages like me or just an enthusiastic cs nerd in general, youâ€™re probably at least a little interested in writing your own fun programming language. Does this ring true for you? If so, join our workshop where we will start by reviewing the key components and principles of what makes a programming language, develop a roadmap to implement those ideas, and then give you guys a chance to give it a go on your own.

title: Compiling the Code
text: A computer archecture introduction. We will be learning how computer software works from binary to high-level languages

title: The Potential for AI in Finance
text: We will use AI to create an investment portfolio . Using AI we will ask those who choose to participate to choose an industry within the public market and then from there choose a stock. With the help of AI they will analyze the companies 10k report (their yearly report) and create a pitch deck to sell the stock to the rest of the club.

title: Machine Learning

title: Prompt Engineering: Incorporating ChatGPT into your programs
text: We'll learn how to design a website with dynamic features that are linked to OpenAI's chatgpt!
